      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index comparison — pump operating envelope",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values were compared against hemolysis measurements drawn from a multi-centre registry of clinical CPB procedures. The observational dataset spans 847 patient records from three cardiac surgery centres, covering pump speeds of 2000–3500 RPM and flow rates of 3–6 L/min. Agreement between CFD predictions and the registry-derived hemolysis indices was within 12% across all five target flow-speed combinations, with RH < 1 satisfied in each case. The breadth and clinical provenance of the dataset were judged to provide strong support for the model's predictive fidelity under CPB conditions.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/cpb-registry-observational-study",
        "type": "Activity",
        "activityType": "observational-study",
        "name": "Multi-centre CPB registry hemolysis data collection",
        "description": "Retrospective extraction and analysis of hemolysis biomarker data (plasma free haemoglobin, lactate dehydrogenase) from clinical CPB registry records across three cardiac surgery centres. Data were stratified by pump model, speed, and flow rate to construct empirical hemolysis index distributions for comparison with CFD outputs. No experimental conditions were controlled or manipulated by the study team; data reflect routine clinical practice."
      },
      "resultSummary": "CFD RH predictions agree with registry-derived hemolysis indices within 12% across all five operating points; RH < 1 criterion met.",
      "outcomeStatus": "passed"
    }
