    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. The hemolysis index predictions satisfy the RH < 1 acceptance criterion across all five COU operating points. Validation evidence drawn from a large multi-centre clinical registry provides extensive real-world coverage of the operating envelope. The assessment team considered the breadth and clinical provenance of the observational dataset to be a strength of this credibility package, providing greater ecological validity than a single-laboratory bench test. On this basis the CFD model is accepted as credible for the stated COU.",
